<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Metaphor on</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/tags/metaphor/</link><description>Recent content in Metaphor on</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><managingEditor>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</managingEditor><webMaster>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</webMaster><copyright>© 2026 Dr. Hari Thapliyaal</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 01 May 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://dasarpai.github.io/tags/metaphor/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Biological Footprint of Human</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/biological-footprint-of-human/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 May 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/biological-footprint-of-human/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5188-Biological-Footprint-Of-Human.jpg" alt="Biological Footprint of Human" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">Biological Footprint of Human
&lt;div id="biological-footprint-of-human" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#biological-footprint-of-human" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Birds fly in the sky without footprint, &lt;br>
Animals cannot walk on the earth without a footprint. &lt;br>
Those who want to fly don&amp;rsquo;t create a nest to live but to rest. &lt;br>
Those who want to walk create a den and die in those dens.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Death happen to birds also &lt;br>
But, their living noticed by everyone &lt;br>
and death known to none. &lt;br>
Death happens to animal also &lt;br>
They leave a rotten body behind &lt;br>
for other animals to eat.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Do I Have Free Will?</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/do-i-have-free-will/</link><pubDate>Sat, 15 Feb 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/do-i-have-free-will/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5118-Do-I-Have-Free-Will.jpg" alt="Do I Have Free Will?" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">Do I Have Free Will?
&lt;div id="do-i-have-free-will" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#do-i-have-free-will" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Since the time first life came in the existence, &lt;br>
It is struggling to establish itself separate &lt;br>
from the existence, it came from!&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Like drop comes out of the ocean &lt;br>
And it is struggling to establish its Independence from the ocean. &lt;br>
We all know where the drop has come from &lt;br>
and what happens to the drop at the end.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Saving The Moon</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/saving-the-moon/</link><pubDate>Wed, 04 Dec 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/saving-the-moon/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5113-Saving-The-Moon.jpg" alt="Saving The Moon" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">Saving The Moon
&lt;div id="saving-the-moon" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#saving-the-moon" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>You know my friend Pratibimba, &lt;br>
He is a big man, but sometimes &lt;br>
he behaves like a child and too naive about the reality around. &lt;br>
Once upon a time, &lt;br>
It was the day of the festival and late evening &lt;br>
and he was traveling through a forest &lt;br>
Long he traveled and feeling thirsty.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Dissolving A Drop In The Ocean</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/dissolving-a-drop-in-the-ocean/</link><pubDate>Sun, 10 Nov 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/dissolving-a-drop-in-the-ocean/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5111-Dissolving-A-Drop-In-The-Ocean.jpg" alt="Dissolving A Drop In The Ocean" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">Dissolving A Drop In The Ocean
&lt;div id="dissolving-a-drop-in-the-ocean" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#dissolving-a-drop-in-the-ocean" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Some drops are hard as stone &lt;br>
It takes millions of years to make &lt;br>
them and millions to dissolve.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Some drops are like salt ball &lt;br>
It takes longer to make them &lt;br>
but they dissolve quickly.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Some drops have a dirty smell &lt;br>
When those merge into the ocean &lt;br>
for some time there is a bad smell around them &lt;br>
but very soon they also disappear.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Eyes On The Ground</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/eyes-on-the-ground/</link><pubDate>Mon, 15 Apr 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/eyes-on-the-ground/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5095-Eyes-On-The-Ground.jpg" alt="Eyes On The Ground" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">Eyes On The Ground
&lt;div id="eyes-on-the-ground" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#eyes-on-the-ground" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Whether I walk, jog or run &lt;br>
If I have continuous eyes on the ground &lt;br>
I will not fall because of environmental reasons.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I may still fall but the cause will be &lt;br>
either my weak limbs or my foolishness. &lt;br>
But I am happy with this, &lt;br>
because I am in control &lt;br>
and I know my happiness &lt;br>
and miseries are 100% my doing.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>